cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the application of practical computing to problems in computational complexity and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Other likely sub-categories include cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
